subSubSection.paragraph:
Etymology. The derivation of the specific name is not mentioned in the publication in which this species was originally described based on eggs (
Causey et al ., 1944
), but the authors clearly state in a second paper (
Causey et al ., 1945
) that the species was named in honour of Lloyd E. Rozeboom. The late Prof. Rozeboom was a renowned medical entomologist at Johns Hopkins University School of Hygiene and Public Health in Baltimore, Maryland, USA .

